2026-04-16 12:32:20 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['load protection diode (load module)'] hypothesis_explanation='The voltage across the load protection diode (0.359 V anode, 0.0003 V cathode) indicates a low forward voltage and strongly suggests excessive voltage drop, not allowing enough voltage/current to reach the load even with the relay output at nearly 12 V. This value is atypically low for a normal silicon diode (expected ~0.6-0.7 V) and similar to what can happen if the diode is damaged (shorting partially or degraded junction), causing intermittent or resistive behavior. Previous data show that all wiring and relay controls, as well as both the internal and external lamps, lack supply voltage even when the control relay is closed and the sensor is working. No mechanical or wiring fault is present. Therefore, a partially shorted or degraded protection diode in the load module is the most likely cause of the symptoms.'
